The MUNIO, or Minio, now the Mignone, takes its rise on the high ground to the west of the Lago di Bracciano, and falls into the sea between Civita Vecchia and the mouth of the river Marta, near a watch-tower‚ Terre Bertaldo, known also as Sant' Agostino, from a legend that here an angel dispelled St. Augustine’s doubts respecting the Trinity.
